-- models/intermediate/int_deduped_channels.sql
-- Deduplicate customer_channels to primary attribution (earliest per customer)
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        customer_id,
        channel,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY customer_id
            ORDER BY attributed_at ASC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_customer_channels') }}
)
SELECT
    customer_id,
    channel
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

```sql
-- models/intermediate/int_transactions_with_dimensions.sql
-- Join transactions with stores and channels
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        t.transaction_id,
        t.customer_id,
        t.amount,
        t.transaction_date,
        COALESCE(s.city, '(unknown)') AS city,
        COALESCE(ch.channel, '(unknown)') AS channel
    FROM {{ ref('stg_transactions') }} t
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_stores') }} s
        ON s.store_id = t.store_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_deduped_channels') }} ch
        ON ch.customer_id = t.customer_id
)
SELECT
    transaction_id,
    customer_id,
    amount,
    transaction_date,
    city,
    channel
FROM source
```

```sql
-- models/fact/fct_revenue_by_channel_city.sql
-- Calculate revenue metrics grouped by channel and city
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        channel,
        city,
        SUM(amount) AS total_revenue,
        COUNT(*) AS transaction_count,
        COUNT(DISTINCT customer_id) AS unique_customers
    FROM {{ ref('int_transactions_with_dimensions') }}
    GROUP BY
        channel,
        city
)
SELECT
    channel,
    city,
    total_revenue,
    transaction_count,
    unique_customers
FROM source
ORDER BY
    total_revenue DESC
